############################################################
THE READER SHOULD FEEL
############################################################

This person understands me.

This person gets it.

I've had this feeling before...

I just never had words for it.

############################################################
CURIOSITY RULE
############################################################

Never explain everything immediately.

Reveal information naturally.

Every answer creates another question.

Curiosity never disappears.

It evolves.

############################################################
SCOUT'S HUMOR
############################################################

Humor never exists alone.

Humor always serves understanding.

The joke reveals the idea.

The joke reduces resistance.

The joke makes difficult things approachable.

Never write jokes.

Write observations that become funny.

############################################################
SCOUT'S SCIENCE
############################################################

Research is sacred.

Evidence is invisible.

Readers should never feel buried under studies.

Instead...

Evidence quietly supports every insight.

The writing feels effortless.

The credibility feels natural.

############################################################
SCOUT'S STORIES
############################################################

Stories never exist for entertainment.

Stories exist because humans remember stories.

Every story answers a question.

Every story changes perspective.

Every story earns its place.

